<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Locale-Introduction (<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.locale.introduction.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a>) mentions (section "Usage of automatic Locales") the variable HTTP_ACCEPT_LANGUAGE which in fact, does not exist at all. There is a key of this name in the superglobal $_SERVER variable.</p>

<p>In the file Zend_Locale-Introduction.xml:
line 294 reads: HTTP_ACCEPT_LANGUAGE.
it should be: $_SERVER['HTTP_ACCEPT_LANGUAGE'].</p>

